let _markdown = "\n\n# Chr3D Python API Reference\n\nChr3D provides a comprehensive Python API for analyzing 3D chromatin conformation data from ChIA-PET, HiChIP, and Hi-C experiments.\n\n## Installation\n\n```python\npip install chr3d\n```\n\n## Core Modules\n\n### Pipeline Classes\n\n| Module                    | Description                                             |\n| ------------------------- | ------------------------------------------------------- |\n| [ChIA-PET API](./chiapet) | Linker filtering, mapping, loop calling for ChIA-PET    |\n| [HiChIP API](./hichip)    | Restriction-based purification, loop calling for HiChIP |\n| [Hi-C API](./hic)         | Contact matrix generation for Hi-C                      |\n| [Utilities](./utils)      | Helper functions and common operations                  |\n\n## Quick Start Examples\n\n### ChIA-PET Analysis\n\n```python\nimport sys\nsys.path.insert(0, '/path/to/Chr3D/src')\n\nfrom chr3d.linker_filtering_v3 import LinkerFilterV3\nfrom chr3d.mapping_v2 import PETMapper\nfrom chr3d.chiapet_purifying import ChIAPETPurifier\nfrom chr3d.pet_categorization import PETCategorizer\nfrom chr3d.peak_calling import PeakCaller\nfrom chr3d.loop_calling import PreClusterer, AnchorClusterer, StatisticalSignificance\n\n# Step 1: Filter linkers\nlinker_filter = LinkerFilterV3(\n    linker_sequences=['ACGCGATATCTTATCTGACT', 'AGTCAGATAAGATATCGCGT'],\n    n_threads=8\n)\nstats = linker_filter.filter_fastq_parallel(\n    fastq_r1='sample_R1.fastq.gz',\n    fastq_r2='sample_R2.fastq.gz',\n    output_prefix='filtered',\n    output_dir='./output'\n)\n\n# Continue with mapping, purifying, categorization, peak calling, loop calling...\n```\n\n### HiChIP Analysis\n\n```python\nfrom chr3d.mapping_v2 import PETMapper\nfrom chr3d.hichip_purifying import HiChIPPurifier\nfrom chr3d.pet_categorization import PETCategorizer\nfrom chr3d.peak_calling import PeakCaller\nfrom chr3d.loop_calling import PreClusterer, AnchorClusterer, StatisticalSignificance\n\n# Step 1: Map reads (no linker filtering for HiChIP)\nmapper = PETMapper(\n    genome_index='/ref/hg38.fa',\n    mapping_quality_cutoff=30,\n    n_threads=8,\n    use_bwa_mem=True\n)\nmap_stats = mapper.map_linker_filtered_fastq(\n    fastq_r1='sample_R1.fastq.gz',\n    fastq_r2='sample_R2.fastq.gz',\n    output_prefix='mapped',\n    output_dir='./output/mapping'\n)\n\n# Step 2: Purify (remove same-fragment PETs)\npurifier = HiChIPPurifier(restriction_file='/ref/hg38_MboI_sites.bed')\npurify_stats = purifier.remove_same_fragment_pets(\n    './output/mapping/mapped.dedup.bedpe',\n    './output/purified.valid.bedpe',\n    './output/purified.sameres.bedpe'\n)\n\n# Continue with categorization, peak calling, loop calling...\n```\n\n### Hi-C Analysis\n\n```python\nfrom chr3d.bulk_hic import HiCPipeline\n\n# Initialize pipeline\nhic_pipeline = HiCPipeline(\n    genome_index='/ref/hg38.fa',\n    chrom_sizes='/ref/hg38.chrom.sizes',\n    threads=8,\n    assembly='hg38',\n    min_mapq=30,\n    min_distance=1000,\n    resolutions=[1000, 5000, 10000, 25000, 50000]\n)\n\n# Run complete pipeline\nstats = hic_pipeline.run(\n    fastq1='sample_R1.fastq.gz',\n    fastq2='sample_R2.fastq.gz',\n    output_dir='./output',\n    sample_id='HiC_sample',\n    cleanup=True\n)\n```\n\n## Module Overview\n\n### Linker Filtering (`chr3d.linker_filtering_v3`)\n\nHigh-performance linker detection and filtering for ChIA-PET data.\n\n```python\nfrom chr3d.linker_filtering_v3 import LinkerFilterV3\n\nfilter = LinkerFilterV3(\n    linker_sequences=['ACGCGATATCTTATCTGACT'],\n    min_alignment_score=14,\n    min_tag_length=18,\n    max_tag_length=1000,\n    n_threads=8\n)\n```\n\n### Mapping (`chr3d.mapping_v2`)\n\nBWA-based read mapping with BEDPE generation.\n\n```python\nfrom chr3d.mapping_v2 import PETMapper\n\nmapper = PETMapper(\n    genome_index='/ref/hg38.fa',\n    mapping_quality_cutoff=30,\n    n_threads=8,\n    use_bwa_mem=True,\n    self_ligation_cutoff=8000\n)\n```\n\n### Purification\n\n#### ChIA-PET (`chr3d.chiapet_purifying`)\n\n```python\nfrom chr3d.chiapet_purifying import ChIAPETPurifier\npurifier = ChIAPETPurifier(merge_distance=2)\n```\n\n#### HiChIP (`chr3d.hichip_purifying`)\n\n```python\nfrom chr3d.hichip_purifying import HiChIPPurifier\npurifier = HiChIPPurifier(restriction_file='/ref/hg38_MboI_sites.bed')\n```\n\n### PET Categorization (`chr3d.pet_categorization`)\n\nClassifies PETs into iPET, sPET, and oPET categories.\n\n```python\nfrom chr3d.pet_categorization import PETCategorizer\n\ncategorizer = PETCategorizer(\n    self_ligation_cutoff=1000,  # 1kb for HiChIP, 8kb for ChIA-PET\n    mode='hichip'  # or 'chiapet'\n)\n```\n\n### Peak Calling (`chr3d.peak_calling`)\n\nMACS3-based peak calling from self-ligation PETs.\n\n```python\nfrom chr3d.peak_calling import PeakCaller\n\npeak_caller = PeakCaller(\n    genome_size='hs',\n    qvalue_cutoff=0.05,\n    keep_dup='all'\n)\n```\n\n### Loop Calling (`chr3d.loop_calling`)\n\nStatistical loop calling with FDR correction.\n\n```python\nfrom chr3d.loop_calling import PreClusterer, AnchorClusterer, StatisticalSignificance\n\n# Pre-clustering\npre_clusterer = PreClusterer(extension_length=500)\nprecluster_stats = pre_clusterer.pre_cluster(ipet_file, output_prefix)\n\n# Anchor clustering\nanchor_clusterer = AnchorClusterer()\ncluster_stats = anchor_clusterer.cluster_anchors(precluster_file, cluster_file)\n\n# Statistical significance\nstat_sig = StatisticalSignificance(\n    ipet_count_threshold=2,\n    pvalue_cutoff=0.05,\n    extension_length=500,\n    use_distance_correction=True  # For HiChIP\n)\nsig_stats = stat_sig.calculate_significance(cluster_file, ipet_file, output_prefix)\n```\n\n### Hi-C Pipeline (`chr3d.bulk_hic`)\n\nComplete Hi-C processing with pairtools and cooler.\n\n```python\nfrom chr3d.bulk_hic import HiCPipeline\n\npipeline = HiCPipeline(\n    genome_index='/ref/hg38.fa',\n    chrom_sizes='/ref/hg38.chrom.sizes',\n    threads=8,\n    resolutions=[1000, 5000, 10000]\n)\n```\n\n## Return Values\n\nMost methods return dictionaries with statistics:\n\n```python\n# Example mapping stats\n{\n    'total_pets': 1000000,\n    'unique_pets': 800000,\n    'duplicate_rate': 0.2,\n    'cis_ratio': 0.85\n}\n\n# Example loop calling stats\n{\n    'total_loops': 5000,\n    'significant_loops': 1500,\n    'fdr_threshold': 0.05\n}\n```\n\n## Error Handling\n\n```python\ntry:\n    stats = mapper.map_linker_filtered_fastq(...)\nexcept FileNotFoundError as e:\n    print(f\"Input file not found: {e}\")\nexcept ValueError as e:\n    print(f\"Invalid parameter: {e}\")\n```\n\n## Logging\n\nChr3D uses Python's logging module:\n\n```python\nimport logging\n\n# Enable debug logging\nlogging.basicConfig(level=logging.DEBUG)\n\n# Or configure specific logger\nlogger = logging.getLogger('chr3d')\nlogger.setLevel(logging.INFO)\n```\n";
